  "text": "Regeneration with new attachment became a reality with the introduction of guided tissue regeneration (GTR) technique andcreated interest in membranes, as these maintained space and formed a key to regeneration. Placement of a mechanical barrier such as a membrane, over an osseous defect can prevent proliferating oral epithelium and gingival connective tissue from growing into the defect. Proliferating cells with osteogenic potential can then repopulate the defect resulting in more predictable bone repair [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
